  "texts": [
    "Unlike previous models that were limited to specific tasks, LLMs are adept at a wide range of tasks, from general language processing to domain-specific applications.",
    "The inception of these architectures traces back to significant work in the field of natural language processing, particularly the introduction of the transformer model by Vaswani et al. (2017, pp. 2-4).",
    "Most LLMs share similar model architectures, based on the transformer architecture, however, the key distinction of LLMs lies in their significantly larger scale in terms of model size, data used for training, and computational power.",
    "This scaling enables them to better comprehend natural language and generate high-quality text based on given contexts or prompts.",
    "Furthermore, these billionparameter models, despite being resource-intensive, are surprisingly user-friendly."
  ],
